DOMAIN_SEPARATOR().details: Returns the domain separator for the current chain.

__init__(string,string,string,string).details: To omit the opcodes for checking the `msg.value` in the creation-time EVM bytecode, the constructor is declared as `payable`.

params.name_: The maximum 25-character user-readable string name of the token.
params.name_eip712_: The maximum 50-character user-readable string name of the signing domain, i.e. the name of the dApp or protocol.
params.symbol_: The maximum 5-character user-readable string symbol of the token.
params.version_eip712_: The maximum 20-character current main version of the signing domain. Signatures from different versions are not compatible.

approve(address,uint256).details: Sets `amount` as the allowance of `spender` over the caller's tokens.

eip712Domain().details: Returns the fields and values that describe the domain separator used by this contract for EIP-712 signatures.

returns._0: bytes1 The 1-byte bit map where bit `i` is set to 1 if and only if domain field `i` is present (`0 ≤ i ≤ 4`).
returns._1: String The maximum 50-character user-readable string name of the signing domain, i.e. the name of the dApp or protocol.
returns._2: String The maximum 20-character current main version of the signing domain. Signatures from different versions are not compatible.
returns._4: address The 20-byte address of the verifying contract.
returns._5: bytes32 The 32-byte disambiguation salt for the protocol.
returns._6: DynArray The 32-byte array of EIP-712 extensions.

mint(address).details: Mints `1` token and assigns them to `to` address.

one_vote().details: Returns one vote, to be used by a voter.

returns._0: uint256 Returns one vote, with its decimal value.

permit(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.details: Sets `amount` as the allowance of `spender` over `owner`'s tokens, given `owner`'s signed approval.

params.amount: The 32-byte token amount that is allowed to be spent by the `spender`.
params.deadline: The 32-byte block timestamp up which the `spender` is allowed to spend `amount`.

renounce_ownership().details: Leaves the contract without an owner.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Moves `amount` tokens from the caller's account to `to`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Moves `amount` tokens from `owner` to `to` using the allowance mechanism. The `amount` is then deducted from the caller's allowance.

params.amount: The 32-byte token amount to be transferred.

returns._0: bool The verification whether the transfer succeeded or failed. Note that the function reverts instead of returning `False` on a failure.

transfer_ownership(address).details: Transfers the ownership of the contract to a new account `new_owner`.

params.new_owner: The 20-byte address of the new owner.

20.dev: dev: Cannot send ether to non-payable function

23.dev: dev: Cannot send ether to non-payable function

__init__(string,string,string,string).notice: The initial supply of the token as well as the `owner` role will be assigned to the `msg.sender`.

eip712Domain().notice: The bits in the 1-byte bit map are read from the least significant to the most significant, and fields are indexed in the order that is specified by EIP-712, identical to the order in which they are listed in the function type.

mint(address).notice: Only the owner can access this function. Note that `owner` cannot be the zero address.

permit(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.notice: Note that `spender` cannot be the zero address. Also, `deadline` must be a block timestamp in the future. `v`, `r`, and `s` must be a valid secp256k1 signature from `owner` over the EIP-712-formatted function arguments. Eventually, the signature must use `owner`'s current nonce.

renounce_ownership().notice: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Note that `owner` and `to` cannot be the zero address. Also, `owner` must have a balance of at least `amount`. Eventually, the caller must have allowance for `owner`'s tokens of at least `amount`. WARNING: The function does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`.

transfer_ownership(address).notice: Note that this function can only be called by the current `owner`. Also, the `new_owner` cannot be the zero address.
